The paper deals with subgroup discovery, which is a common topic in machine learning and data mining. The focus is on optimizing the error or target variable dispersion of the groups found, which is relevant to several sub-categories. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are the most likely categories, as they cover the general area of the paper. cs.DM (Data Mining) is also a possibility, as subgroup discovery is a common task in this field. cs.DB (Databases) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) are less likely but still possible, as they can be related to the data analysis and optimization aspects of the paper.
